{
  "summary": "This paper introduces Instruction Tuning (FLAN), a method to significantly enhance the zero-shot learning capabilities of large language models by fine-tuning them on a diverse collection of NLP datasets presented in an instructional format. The 137B parameter FLAN model demonstrates superior zero-shot performance over GPT-3 on numerous tasks, highlighting the importance of model scale and diverse task exposure, and aims to bridge the gap between pre-training and prompting.",
  "strengths": [
    {
      "point": "Demonstrates substantial improvement in zero-shot performance",
