    },
    {
      "point": "Provides key insights into factors influencing instruction tuning success",
      "evidence": "Ablation studies reveal the importance of the number and diversity of task clusters, and critically, that benefits only emerge with sufficient model scale (100B+ models showed significant improvements, while smaller models degraded)."
    },
    {
      "point": "Created a high-performing model setting new benchmarks",
      "evidence": "The creation of FLAN, a 137B parameter instruction-tuned model, which sets new benchmarks for zero-shot performance on many tasks."
