    {
      "point": "Acknowledged as a catalyst for further research",
      "evidence": "The work aims to stimulate more research into instruction-based NLP, zero-shot learning, and the use of labeled data to enhance the general-purpose capabilities of large language models."
    }
  ],
  "weaknesses": [
    {
      "point": "Lacks clear distinction from established multi-task learning",
      "evidence": "The paper does not sufficiently articulate how instruction tuning fundamentally differs from multi-task learning (e.g., T5's text-to-text approach) beyond superficial format conversion, nor does it offer a cognitive or linguistic theory for the 'instruction' effect."
