    {
      "point": "Subjectivity, bias, and reproducibility issues in template design",
      "evidence": "The reliance on 'manually composed, diverse natural language instruction templates' introduces subjectivity and potential human bias. Lack of details on guidelines, diversity criteria, inter-annotator agreement, and concrete examples compromises reproducibility and assessment of quality."
    },
    {
      "point": "Insufficient detail on training mix and hyperparameters",
      "evidence": "The 'specific mixing scheme' and crucial training hyperparameters (learning rate schedule, optimizer details, exact batch size) are vaguely described or omitted, making reproduction of the 137B model highly improbable."
